The paper discusses a new logic-based approach to incorporating domain knowledge in machine learning, which is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science. The use of Stochastic Gradient Descent and Markov Chain Monte Carlo techniques suggests a focus on artificial intelligence and machine learning (cs.AI, cs.LG), while the use of logical independence assumptions and the development of a new logic suggests a focus on logic and verification (cs.LO). The mention of network synthesis and analysis in a bioinformatics project suggests a possible focus on systems and control (cs.SY) or databases (cs.DB).
